      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose what I\u0027m saying here is that either name them both SkUTF8_NextUnichar and go on a quest to remove the one argument version, or turn these into actual iterators or spans or ranges or whatever works nicely here. On the other hand, after looking around I can\u0027t say I see any shining examples of this sort of iterator that I like. I know we generally frown on overloading, but I\u0027m fine with it since we\u0027re trying to get rid of one of them. On the other hand, maybe just SkUTF8_Next would be fine, since that is obviously (at least to me) going to read in a utf8 and return an SkUnichar. It\u0027s also shorter.\n\nNote that icu has UTF8_NEXT which turns into http://icu-project.org/apiref/icu4c/utf8_8h.html#a27c3748113bc63347a7fa3a4b2c71029 . Note that this is more or less the same as the two argument version of SkUTF8_NextUnichar (except that its a macro so can do weird things).",
